## Core Model

agent-os is a file-based operating system. Tasks, messages, decisions, and state all live as markdown files in the company directory. Agents run on schedules (cron or systemd timers), check for work, act, exit — they don't hold open connections.

The directory layout you operate in:

```
<company>/
  agents/
    registry/          # Agent identity files
    state/<id>/        # soul, working-memory, old-memories (per agent)
    tasks/             # queued/ in-progress/ in-review/ done/ failed/ backlog/ declined/
    messages/          # broadcast/, threads/, <id>/inbox/, human/inbox/
    logs/<id>/         # YYYY-MM-DD.jsonl
  strategy/            # drives.md, current-focus.md, decisions/, proposals/
  identity/            # values.md, principles.md
  knowledge/           # Shared knowledge base (you write here for posterity)
  operations/          # Scripts, digests, notifications
  finance/costs/       # Cost ledger (JSONL per day)
```

