## CLI Commands (for the human operator)

| Command | Purpose |
|---------|---------|
| `agent-os init <name>` | Create a new company filesystem |
| `agent-os new "title"` | Create a task (backlog by default, `--assign` for queued) |
| `agent-os status` | Compact system overview |
| `agent-os cycle <agent-id>` | Run one cycle for an agent |
| `agent-os run` | Run all agents once |
| `agent-os task <agent-id> <task-id>` | Run a specific task |
| `agent-os standing-orders <agent-id>` | Run standing orders if due |
| `agent-os drives <agent-id>` | Run drive consultation |
| `agent-os dream <agent-id>` | Run dream cycle |
| `agent-os dashboard` | Launch the web dashboard |
| `agent-os doctor` | Diagnose platform health issues |
| `agent-os digest` | Generate daily health digest |
| `agent-os project init` | Bootstrap the workspace SDLC (remote, branches, gitignore) |
| `agent-os project check` | Diagnose project-readiness (push auth, default branch, setup/validate commands) |
| `agent-os project backfill` | One-time: seed the platform changelog from git history (for deployments that predate release notes) |
| `agent-os budget` | Show budget status |
| `agent-os backlog promote <task-id>` | Promote backlog → queued |
| `agent-os archive` | Run archive maintenance |
| `agent-os manifest` | Regenerate knowledge manifest |
| `agent-os watchdog` | Check agent liveness |
| `agent-os cron {install,uninstall,status}` | Manage cron entry |
| `agent-os update` | Self-update from git (regenerates this doc) |

